                <p><span class="font-weight-700">The Power of the Crossplane Concept (CP2)</span></p>
                <p>What sets this engine apart is the <span class="font-weight-700">270-degree crossplane concept (CP2) </span>crankshaft. Unlike a conventional parallel-twin, this design mimics the power pulses of a V-twin engine. The result is a highly irregular firing interval that delivers two key advantages:</p>
                <ol start="1">
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Phenomenal Torque Delivery: </span>The R7 offers a strong, linear surge of torque right from the bottom end of the rev range. This means the power is always accessible and incredibly usable, making it easy to rocket out of corners without constantly rowing through the gearbox.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Unique Exhaust Note:</span> The 270-degree crank gives the bike a distinctive, throaty growl—a sound that is arguably more characterful and exciting than the generic inline-four scream, adding to the overall sensory experience.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>With peak power of <span class="font-weight-700">73.4 PS </span>and a robust torque figure of <span class="font-weight-700">67 Nm,</span> the R7 doesn't chase peak horsepower numbers. Instead, it focuses on the quality of power delivery, creating a thrilling yet predictable ride that is ideal for honing track skills.</p>
