                <h3 class="subheading">Chassis, Suspension, and Handling: Precision Engineering</h3>
                <p>While the engine is familiar, the R7's chassis and running gear are all new and track-focused, distinguishing it completely from its MT-07 sibling. This is where Yamaha engineers ensured the R7 earns its supersport moniker.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Track-Ready Suspension</span></p>
                <p>The R7 boasts a high-specification, fully adjustable suspension setup. The front features a <span class="font-weight-700">41mm KYB upside-down (USD) fork </span>which is adjustable for <span class="font-weight-700">preload, rebound, and compression. </span>This level of adjustability is a massive selling point in this class, allowing serious riders to meticulously fine-tune the front end for different track layouts or riding conditions.</p>
                <p>At the rear, the<span class="font-weight-700"> Linked-type Monocross shock absorber </span>is similarly adjustable for <span class="font-weight-700">preload and rebound. </span>This setup ensures the bike maintains exceptional stability and chassis composure, offering a predictable feel when pushing the limits on the tarmac.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Lightweight Frame and Brakes</span></p>
                <p>The chassis is a slim, diamond-type (tubular steel) frame that has been optimized for rigidity and lightness. With a kerb weight of just <span class="font-weight-700">188 kg (wet), </span>the R7 undercuts most of its middleweight competition, making it incredibly agile and easy to flick from side to side.</p>
                <p>Braking duties are handled by a premium setup: dual <span class="font-weight-700">298mm front discs </span>with radial-mount four-piston calipers, complemented by a single <span class="font-weight-700">245mm rear disc. </span>Crucially, the system uses an<span class="font-weight-700"> ABS (Anti-lock Braking System) </span>and is operated by a premium <span class="font-weight-700">Brembo radial master cylinder. </span>The combination provides superb stopping power, consistent feel, and a level of refinement usually seen on more expensive superbikes.</p>
